---
<BaseLayout title="Pricing — Codebolt" navbarVariant="solid" site={site} navigation={navigation}>
  <PageHeader
    title="Pricing"
    subtitle="Use the engine for free with your own keys. Add managed AI, sandboxes, memory, and team controls when you need them."
  />
  <CenteredText
    variant="thesis"
    text="Codebolt is free to run as an application and cloud workspace in BYOK mode. Paid plans are for managed AI capacity and team infrastructure: model routing across small, fast, text-specialized, coding, embedding, and frontier models; cloud sandboxes; cloud memory; and shared administration."
  />
  <PricingGrid
    tabs={[{"label":"Individual","cards":[{"tier":"BYOK","price":"Always free","for":"Bring your own model keys. Use Codebolt's apps and cloud surfaces without paying Codebolt for AI usage.","features":["Codebolt Editor, CLI, Cloud, and SDK","All core features included","Use your own OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, local, or provider keys","Run agents, plugins, memory, and workflows","Local and self-hosted friendly","No Codebolt markup on your own keys"],"cta":{"label":"Start Free","href":"/download","variant":"secondary"}},{"tier":"Pro","price":"$20","price_sub":"/mo","for":"Managed AI credits for builders who want batteries included instead of managing provider keys.","featured":true,"badge":"Early access","features":["Managed AI APIs and embeddings","Cloud memory and cloud sandboxes","Automatic routing across small, fast, text, coding, embedding, and frontier models","Lower effective model cost than using one large model for every task","Use BYOK alongside managed Codebolt capacity","Plan not active yet; request early access"],"cta":{"label":"Request Early Access","href":"#request-access","variant":"primary","waitlist":true,"plan":"pro","audience":"individual"}},{"tier":"Max","price":"From $100","price_sub":"/mo","for":"More managed capacity for heavier agent work, larger runs, and more cloud execution.","badge":"Higher limits","options":[{"label":"Max 5x","price":"$100/mo","description":"More managed AI, embeddings, memory, and sandbox capacity for frequent individual use."},{"label":"Max 20x","price":"$200/mo","description":"Highest individual capacity for heavier multi-agent runs and longer cloud work."}],"features":["Everything in Pro","Higher included managed AI capacity","More cloud sandbox and cloud memory usage","Better fit for long-running or parallel agent workflows","Same multi-model routing strategy to reduce waste","Plan not active yet; request early access"],"cta":{"label":"Request Early Access","href":"#request-access","variant":"secondary","waitlist":true,"plan":"max","audience":"individual"}}]},{"label":"Team","cards":[{"tier":"Team BYOK","price":"$10","price_sub":"/seat/mo","for":"Teams that want shared BYOK administration, collaboration controls, and team-level workspace features.","featured":true,"badge":"BYOK for teams","features":["Everything in individual BYOK","Shared provider keys managed at team level","Team workspaces and access controls","Shared agents, plugins, and workflows","Usage visibility for team-owned keys","Designed for teams that already have provider contracts"],"cta":{"label":"Request Early Access","href":"#request-access","variant":"primary","waitlist":true,"plan":"team-byok","audience":"team"}},{"tier":"Enterprise","price":"Custom","for":"Organizations deploying Codebolt across teams, infrastructure, compliance boundaries, or private environments.","features":["Everything in Team BYOK","Custom deployment, self-hosting, and private cloud options","SSO / SAML, audit trails, and policy controls","Custom guardrails and environment templates","Enterprise support and SLA","Commercial terms for larger managed AI capacity"],"cta":{"label":"Contact Us","href":"mailto:contact@codebolt.ai?subject=Codebolt%20Enterprise","variant":"secondary"}}]}]}
  />
  <Accordion
    heading="FAQ"
    items={[{"question":"How is Codebolt different from Claude Code?","answer":"Claude Code is an agent — a great one. You use it. But you can't customize the agentic loop, run multiple agents, or build applications on top of it. Codebolt is the engine that can do what Claude Code does AND scale to multi-agent orchestration, personal agents, and autonomous companies. Start the same way, grow far beyond."},{"question":"How is Codebolt different from Cursor?","answer":"Cursor is an IDE with built-in AI agents. Great editor, fixed agents. Codebolt is an engine with a built-in IDE — plus CLI, TUI, and headless modes. You write custom agents, install plugins, and scale to multi-agent. Same quality editor (Monaco), far more flexibility."},{"question":"How is Codebolt different from OpenClaw?","answer":"OpenClaw is a personal AI assistant — it manages your inbox, calendar, and daily tasks. Codebolt can do the same thing (run 24/7 with persistent memory and plugins), but the engine also scales to multi-agent orchestration, team coordination, and autonomous companies. OpenClaw is one format. Codebolt is the engine that powers every format."},{"question":"How is Codebolt different from Paperclip?","answer":"Paperclip orchestrates agents but doesn't run them — you still need Claude Code, OpenClaw, Cursor, etc. as the actual agents. Codebolt IS the engine. It runs agents AND orchestrates them. One system instead of five tools stitched together."},{"question":"How is Codebolt different from Hermes Agent?","answer":"Hermes is a self-improving personal agent by Nous Research — great learning loop and multi-platform messaging. Codebolt can do the same (persistent memory, plugins, always-on), but the engine also scales to multi-agent orchestration and autonomous companies. Hermes is one agent. Codebolt is the engine that can run hundreds."},{"question":"How is Codebolt different from Letta?","answer":"Letta is a stateful agent platform — memory-first agents that persist across sessions. Codebolt has the same (3-tier memory, context assembly), plus multi-agent coordination, plugin system, multi-environment scaling, and multiple interface formats (CLI, IDE, TUI, Web). Letta is a great memory system. Codebolt is a complete engine."},{"question":"How is Codebolt different from LangChain or CrewAI?","answer":"LangChain and CrewAI are libraries — you import them into your code. Codebolt is a complete engine — IDE, execution environment, coordination system, and infrastructure. Frameworks give you tools to build agents. Codebolt gives them a place to run, coordinate, and scale."},{"question":"I'm using one agent today. Is this for me?","answer":"Yes. Start with the CLI and one agent. You get more power than any free coding tool because you control the agent loop, not just the prompt. When you're ready for more, the engine scales with you."},{"question":"Can I run this headless in CI/CD?","answer":"Yes. The CLI runs in headless server mode. Spawn environments, run agents, transfer state, monitor progress — all without a GUI."},{"question":"Which AI models does Codebolt support?","answer":"All of them. 17+ cloud providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Mistral, Groq, DeepSeek, etc.) plus local models via Ollama and LM Studio. Per-agent and per-task model selection."},{"question":"Why buy managed Codebolt AI instead of using a single model provider directly?","answer":"A single provider plan usually pushes most work through a few large models. Codebolt can route different steps to different model types: small models for simple tasks, text-focused models for documentation, embedding models for retrieval, coding models for implementation, and frontier models only when they are actually needed. The headline credit is the spend; the effective useful work can feel lower-cost because the engine avoids using the largest model for every operation."}]}
  />
</BaseLayout>
